# Miller Hall Thumbnail Placeholder Rule

When adding a room to `MILLER_ROOMS_WITH_MEDIA` in `millerHallMapping.ts` that does **not** have its own Backblaze photo yet, always use this URL as the `thumbnailUrl` placeholder:

```
https://f005.backblazeb2.com/file/4wallsdorms/Suffolk+University+Dorms/Miller/Floor+2/201+%2B+202/sumiller201-plaque-imp-6.jpg
```

## Example

```typescript
{
  roomNumber: '207',
  title: 'Double Suite',
  thumbnailUrl: 'https://f005.backblazeb2.com/file/4wallsdorms/Suffolk+University+Dorms/Miller/Floor+2/201+%2B+202/sumiller201-plaque-imp-6.jpg',
},
```

## When to apply

- Any new room entry added to `MILLER_ROOMS_WITH_MEDIA` where the real room photo URL is unknown or not yet uploaded.
- Never leave `thumbnailUrl` empty or use a non-Backblaze URL.
- Replace the placeholder later once the real room photo is available in Backblaze.
